For setting up OC cluster locally use crc method.

https://console.redhat.com/
https://console.redhat.com/openshift/create/local
Download Openshift local and install it

crc version
crc delete # Remove previous cluster (if present)
crc config set preset openshift # Configure to use openshift preset
crc setup # Initialize environment for cluster
crc start     # It will ask for pull secret, you can get it from the UI https://console.redhat.com/openshift/create/local
You'll get below output:
--------------
Started the OpenShift cluster.

The server is accessible via web console at:
  https://console-openshift-console.apps-crc.testing

Log in as administrator:
  Username: kubeadmin
  Password: Uxx4f-FnE8E-MQC7F-jxirm

Log in as user:
  Username: developer
  Password: developer

Use the 'oc' command line interface:
  $ eval $(crc oc-env)
  $ oc login -u developer https://api.crc.testing:6443
-------------------------------
You can also get creds using below command:
crc console --credentials
To access the OpenShift Container Platform web console with your default web browser, run the following command:
$ crc console

crc oc-env
eval $(crc oc-env)

oc config current-context
oc config use-context crc-admin
oc whoami
------------------
To run sample app:
oc new-app docker.io/library/nginx:1.26 --name=mynginx     # This will create deployment,service and pod
oc get all -l app=mynginx
oc delete all -l app=mynginx
